The government had in November cancelled the examinations after leaked papers were shared social media. President Lazarus Chakwera directed the national examinations board to investigate how the papers leaked and prepare to re-administer the tests not later than January 2021. The board had suggested a re-administration date of March 2021. On Sunday, the board announced that fresh tests will be administered in January and the rest of the students will report back to school on January 5, 2021. Incoming Form One students will report back on February 1, 2021, to allow the Form Four students to sit for examinations. Students had staged demonstrations across the country after the government cancelled the tests. The examinations begun in October and were due to be completed in mid-November. --BBC--